    "course_title": "INFORMATION: PERSPECTIVES AND CONTEXTS",
    "description": "Provides an introduction to major themes and topics in information studies as well as the language and literature of the field and related disciplines. This course is about information, information agencies, and being an information professional. We look at social, historical, ethical, legal and political issues surrounding information dissemination, use, control, and management.",
